#Text=Australian Gliders glide past China women 's national wheelchair basketball team
#Text=Friday , July 20 , 2012
#Text=Homebush Bay , New South Wales —
#Text=Australia and China battle for the ball following a missed shot Image : Bidgee .
#Text=A Chinese player warms up before the game Image : LauraHale .
#Text=The Rollers warm up before the game Image : LauraHale .
#Text=Leanne del Toso in yellow joins her teammates on the floor during player introductions Image : LauraHale .
#Text=Amber Merritt in green joins her teammates on the floor during player introductions Image : LauraHale .
#Text=The Rollers bring the ball down the floor during the game Image : LauraHale .
#Text=Cobi Crispin shoots the ball Image : LauraHale .

#Text=Earlier today , the Australian Gliders beat the Chinese women 's national wheelchair basketball team 57 – 45 at the Rollers & Gliders World Challenge taking place at the Sport Centre at the Sydney Olympic Park .
#Text=China won the game 's opening tip off but did not score in their first time down the floor .
#Text=Australia 's Sarah Stewart took and missed Australia 's first shot .
#Text=China 's 1.5 point player Li Yanhua eventually made the game 's first basket .
#Text=Cobi Crispin made Australia 's first basket at 6:55 left in the first quarter , successfully turning her basket into a three point play by making her free throw as a result of a personal foul .
#Text=Aggressive first quarter play resulted in four Chinese personal fouls with 5:21 left .
#Text=The first quarter ended 13 – 9 in China 's favour .
#Text=The first half ended 24 – 20 , with China leading .

#Text=China 's lead came with a high level of energy , the bench loudly supporting their players , few substitutions , lots of on the court talk , playing a half court game that involved setting up the defense early and fouling .
#Text=In contrast , Australia played a different first half .
#Text=The team did not yell from the bench or on the court , had many substitutions , ran the shot clock down and played a full court defense .
#Text=The second half contrasted visibly with the first .
#Text=Fewer fouls were made by both teams .
#Text=Australia continued to run the shot clock down but their bench woke up , started cheering loudly for their teammates and made fewer substitutions .
#Text=The Australians tied the game 34 – 34 with 1:54 left in the third quarter .
#Text=China 's answer to the closer game was to start substituting players .
#Text=Tactically , things were little changed as neither team changed their defensive game .
#Text=The game was tied again at 9:01 left in the fourth with a score of 38 – 38 .
#Text=Australia was up 42 – 38 at 7:14 left in the fourth .
#Text=Some of China 's defensive difficulties continued to hold them back , including a player who entered the box early for a second time during a free throw shot by an Australian player .
#Text=The Gliders will play tomorrow at 2:30pm Sydney time in the first place match against an opponent to be determined in a game later today between Germany and Japan .
